TY  - JOUR
T1  - Strategic Learning and the Topology of Social Networks
AU  - Mossel, Elchanan
AU  - Sly, Allan
AU  - Tamuz, Omer
Y1  - 2015/09/01
PY  - 2015
DA  - 2015/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12058
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1755
EP  - 1794
VL  - 83
IS  - 5
KW  - Social learning
KW  - informational externalities
KW  - social networks
KW  - aggregation of information
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12058
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We consider a group of strategic agents who must each repeatedly take one of two possible actions. They learn which of the two actions is preferable from initial private signals and by observing the actions of their neighbors in a social network. We show that the question of whether or not the agents learn efficiently depends on the topology of the social network. In particular, we identify a geometric ?egalitarianism? condition on the social network that guarantees learning in infinite networks, or learning with high probability in large finite networks, in any equilibrium. We also give examples of nonegalitarian networks with equilibria in which learning fails.
ER  - 

