T1  - Truthful Equilibria in Dynamic Bayesian Games
AU  - Hörner, Johannes
AU  - Takahashi, Satoru
AU  - Vieille, Nicolas
Y1  - 2015/09/01
PY  - 2015
DA  - 2015/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12182
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1795
EP  - 1848
VL  - 83
IS  - 5
KW  - Bayesian games
KW  - repeated games
KW  - folk theorem
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA12182
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - This paper characterizes an equilibrium payoff subset for dynamic Bayesian games as discounting vanishes. Monitoring is imperfect, transitions may depend on actions, types may be correlated, and values may be interdependent. The focus is on equilibria in which players report truthfully. The characterization generalizes that for repeated games, reducing the analysis to static Bayesian games with transfers. With independent private values, the restriction to truthful equilibria is without loss, except for the punishment level: if players withhold their information during punishment-like phases, a folk theorem obtains.
ER  - 

